I'm engaged with projects like @YieldGuild , @CyberKongz , @coordinape , @iearnfinance . Some are full anon, some are VC backed, some are a mix. Does this make me a liable person? No

5/6

I personally do not want to have a spotlight on my real self and prefer to keep my faithful bird as a bridge to the virtual world. Why do I need to show what I really look like?

4/6

However, I think it's ok to dox yourself to trusted parties within the space.
I've shown my real face to many builders & known people. I am ok to do so because of reputation and trust.
I have spent enough time interacting with those parties to feel at ease to expose myself.

3/6

I don't need people from the outside world to know who I am in the crypto world. 

I also don't need people from the crypto world to know who I am irl. I value my privacy as well as the privacy of my loved ones.

2/6

I disagree partially regarding your statement.

I am pseudonymous and plan to keep it that way for many reasons.
